==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Ambulacrum
<hw>Am`bu*la"crum</hw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>;
<plu><it>pl.</it> <plw>Ambulacra</plw> <pr>(<?/)</pr>.</plu> <ety>[L.,
an alley or covered way.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>One
of the radical zones of echinoderms, along which run the principal
nerves, blood vessels, and water tubes. These zones usually bear rows of
locomotive suckers or tentacles, which protrude from regular pores. In
star fishes they occupy the grooves along the under side of the
rays.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>One of the suckers on the feet of
mites.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Ambulance</ent>⟦br⟧
